WEBVTT

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:04.000
{\an8}<b><font color="#9CD5FF">One Pace Premium</font></b>
Keep the project alive: <font color="#a8c7fa">ko-fi.com/not6ip</font>

2
00:01:50.050 --> 00:01:58.390
Arlong Park

3
00:02:18.990 --> 00:02:21.750
The weather's so great!

4
00:02:25.420 --> 00:02:29.250
Is the Grand Line
far, far away that way?!

5
00:02:30.550 --> 00:02:32.720
Or maybe this way?!

6
00:02:33.090 --> 00:02:34.840
That way?! This way?!

7
00:02:35.970 --> 00:02:37.680
This is so exciting!

8
00:02:37.680 --> 00:02:39.680
You're annoying.

9
00:02:39.680 --> 00:02:41.140
Sit still, will ya?

10
00:02:41.140 --> 00:02:43.140
Sorry! Sorry!

11
00:02:44.140 --> 00:02:48.900
Now that we finally have a cook,
all we need is to get Nami back!

12
00:02:48.900 --> 00:02:51.110
Then we're finally going
to the Grand Line!

13
00:02:51.730 --> 00:02:53.490
Nami, huh?

14
00:02:53.490 --> 00:02:57.740
The memory of her beautiful visage
is enough to lift my spirits.

15
00:02:58.280 --> 00:03:00.330
How I can't wait to see her again!

16
00:03:02.370 --> 00:03:03.830
Hey, Yosaku.

17
00:03:03.830 --> 00:03:06.290
We're almost to where Nami is, right?

18
00:03:07.580 --> 00:03:10.550
Guys, get serious! This isn't a game!

19
00:03:10.550 --> 00:03:11.750
Don't you get it?!

20
00:03:11.750 --> 00:03:16.840
We're heading right toward the
infamous Arlong's lair as we speak!

21
00:03:19.600 --> 00:03:22.390
When Big Sis spotted
Arlong's wanted poster...

22
00:03:22.390 --> 00:03:24.850
she couldn't take her eyes off it!

23
00:03:26.890 --> 00:03:28.860
She was like a different person!

24
00:03:34.030 --> 00:03:39.700
Big Sis Nami must be after
Arlong's twenty-million-berry bounty!

25
00:03:39.700 --> 00:03:43.540
She may already be inside
his compound as we speak!

26
00:03:45.540 --> 00:03:46.960
Well, let's have some food.

27
00:03:46.960 --> 00:03:47.540
Yeah.

28
00:03:49.830 --> 00:03:53.670
Don't tell me you guys
have never heard of Arlong?!

29
00:03:53.670 --> 00:03:54.840
Arlong?

30
00:03:54.840 --> 00:03:55.590
Dunno.

31
00:04:01.180 --> 00:04:03.010
Alright, listen up!

32
00:04:03.010 --> 00:04:05.850
I guess I'll just have to fill you in!

33
00:04:06.680 --> 00:04:11.190
Arlong is a fishman who used to
rampage throughout the Grand Line!

34
00:04:11.190 --> 00:04:12.190
Fishman?

35
00:04:12.190 --> 00:04:14.820
A fishman, huh? I've never met one.

36
00:04:14.820 --> 00:04:17.650
Y'know, somewhere on
the Grand Line, there's supposedly

37
00:04:17.650 --> 00:04:20.780
a place called Fishman Island
teeming with gorgeous mermaids!

38
00:04:21.160 --> 00:04:22.410
Do fishmen look...

39
00:04:23.280 --> 00:04:24.040
like this?

40
00:04:25.580 --> 00:04:26.790
What a masterpiece!

41
00:04:25.950 --> 00:04:28.250
Can't you guys stay focused?!

42
00:04:28.960 --> 00:04:32.000
Alright, then. Let's start from the top.

43
00:04:32.750 --> 00:04:37.010
First of all, the reason the Grand Line
is called the Pirate Graveyard

44
00:04:37.010 --> 00:04:39.470
is due to three great powers
that rule over it.

45
00:04:39.880 --> 00:04:43.850
One of which is the
Seven Warlords of the Sea!

46
00:04:46.430 --> 00:04:48.230
Seven Warlords?

47
00:04:48.770 --> 00:04:51.690
Simply put, they're
the government's very own pirates.

48
00:04:51.690 --> 00:04:53.270
Are you kidding?

49
00:04:53.270 --> 00:04:57.110
Why would pirates receive
government approval?

50
00:04:57.740 --> 00:05:02.740
They're allowed to roam free because
the government receives a cut

51
00:05:02.740 --> 00:05:04.910
of what they plunder
from other pirates.

52
00:05:05.660 --> 00:05:09.660
To other pirates, they're no more
than government dogs,

53
00:05:09.660 --> 00:05:11.250
but they're incredibly strong!

54
00:05:16.960 --> 00:05:22.590
Counted among them is the man
who defeated Zoro, Hawk Eye Mihawk!

55
00:05:22.590 --> 00:05:24.390
That's just crazy!

56
00:05:24.390 --> 00:05:26.850
There are seven guys like him?!

57
00:05:26.850 --> 00:05:28.600
The Seven Warlords sound crazy!

58
00:05:28.600 --> 00:05:34.560
Well, one of the Seven Warlords
is Jinbe, boss of the Fishman Pirates.

59
00:05:35.230 --> 00:05:38.110
He and Arlong stood
side by side as equals,

60
00:05:38.110 --> 00:05:42.570
committing atrocity after
atrocity in the Grand Line.

61
00:05:44.780 --> 00:05:45.830
Like this?

62
00:05:45.830 --> 00:05:48.790
That's just your last
picture standing up!

63
00:05:49.450 --> 00:05:54.920
Arlong has subjugated twenty towns
since coming to the East Blue!

64
00:05:54.920 --> 00:05:58.750
He makes Don Krieg look like nothing!

65
00:05:59.130 --> 00:06:03.590
But why would Nami go
after this guy on her own?

66
00:06:04.340 --> 00:06:07.220
I told you, she must want
the bounty on his head!

67
00:06:07.220 --> 00:06:08.310
I don't know...

68
00:06:08.310 --> 00:06:11.350
Maybe Nami is actually a mermaid!

69
00:06:11.350 --> 00:06:14.190
She's certainly lovely enough!

70
00:06:14.440 --> 00:06:14.560
Nami

71
00:06:14.560 --> 00:06:14.690
Nami

72
00:06:14.690 --> 00:06:18.190
Nami

73
00:06:14.980 --> 00:06:15.770
Like this?!

74
00:06:15.770 --> 00:06:18.190
I'll kill you, you bastard!

75
00:06:18.570 --> 00:06:22.070
Do you guys even understand
what I just said?!

76
00:06:22.070 --> 00:06:25.160
Yeah, there's a strong
fishman, right? We get it!

77
00:06:25.660 --> 00:06:28.120
No, you don't get it!

78
00:06:28.120 --> 00:06:30.120
You don't know
how strong fishmen are!

79
00:06:30.540 --> 00:06:32.580
We'll find out when we get there.

80
00:06:32.580 --> 00:06:34.080
Quit worrying.

81
00:06:34.580 --> 00:06:37.040
Anyway, let's have some food.

82
00:06:37.500 --> 00:06:39.050
Yeah! Food!

83
00:06:39.670 --> 00:06:40.880
Oh? Food?

84
00:06:41.340 --> 00:06:42.720
What do you want?

85
00:06:42.720 --> 00:06:44.970
I want meat on the bone!

86
00:06:44.970 --> 00:06:46.760
I want sautéed bean sprouts!

87
00:06:46.760 --> 00:06:47.720
Alright!

88
00:06:47.720 --> 00:06:48.680
Leave it to me!

89
00:06:50.310 --> 00:06:51.430
I'll be done in no time!

90
00:06:52.020 --> 00:06:53.310
Meat and bean sprouts...

91
00:06:54.100 --> 00:06:57.400
Having a cook is the best!

92
00:06:57.400 --> 00:06:58.270
Y-Yeah!

93
00:06:58.650 --> 00:07:00.270
Meat! A whole buncha meat!

94
00:07:00.270 --> 00:07:02.780
And bean sprouts for me!
A huge serving!

95
00:07:03.360 --> 00:07:09.740
Northwestern East Blue

96
00:07:16.500 --> 00:07:17.540
Alright.

97
00:07:17.540 --> 00:07:20.290
Here's this month's payment. Take it.

98
00:07:20.340 --> 00:07:26.010
Captain Nezumi
16th Branch, Marines

99
00:07:21.300 --> 00:07:22.800
My dear Arlong.

100
00:07:22.800 --> 00:07:24.880
You have a different approach

101
00:07:24.880 --> 00:07:26.880
than your run-of-the-mill pirates.

102
00:07:26.880 --> 00:07:28.760
You know how the world operates.

103
00:07:28.800 --> 00:07:33.390
Captain "Sawtooth" Arlong
(Saw Shark Fishman)
Arlong Pirates

104
00:07:31.850 --> 00:07:33.470
Likewise!

105
00:07:33.470 --> 00:07:37.730
Befriending me means you can milk
the East Blue for all it's worth!

106
00:07:38.350 --> 00:07:42.690
That's some outside-the-box
thinking for a Marine captain.

107
00:07:43.070 --> 00:07:44.320
Much obliged as ever.

108
00:07:46.320 --> 00:07:47.910
Why the sudden formality?

109
00:07:47.910 --> 00:07:50.660
Money makes the world go round.

110
00:07:51.410 --> 00:07:52.370
Cash is king.

111
00:07:52.370 --> 00:07:54.620
You can trust it more than anything.

112
00:07:55.040 --> 00:07:56.580
Don't you agree?

113
00:07:57.330 --> 00:07:58.710
Indeed...

114
00:07:58.710 --> 00:08:03.670
I hate humans, but good sports
like you are an exception.

115
00:08:04.380 --> 00:08:05.840
Well...

116
00:08:05.840 --> 00:08:06.970
I should be going.

117
00:08:07.470 --> 00:08:09.930
What's the rush?
Stay and have a drink.

118
00:08:10.800 --> 00:08:15.890
Marine patrol ships shouldn't
be seen docking at a pirate's island.

119
00:08:15.890 --> 00:08:19.850
I'll kill anyone who reports
you to headquarters.

120
00:08:19.850 --> 00:08:21.690
No need. I'll be leaving.

121
00:08:22.110 --> 00:08:24.190
Hey, the captain's departing!

122
00:08:24.190 --> 00:08:26.320
Escort him to his ship!

123
00:08:26.320 --> 00:08:27.860
You got it!

124
00:08:26.900 --> 00:08:31.870
Officer Hatchan
(Octopus Fishman)
Arlong Pirates

125
00:08:29.450 --> 00:08:31.870
Get in the octopus pot! I'll take you!

126
00:08:31.870 --> 00:08:34.450
Right. Thanks.

127
00:08:34.450 --> 00:08:37.830
But y'know, I just can't get over
how funny your face is.

128
00:08:37.830 --> 00:08:40.000
It looks just like a rat's!

129
00:08:40.960 --> 00:08:42.670
Hey! Hachi!

130
00:08:42.670 --> 00:08:43.960
Watch your mouth!

131
00:08:43.960 --> 00:08:45.800
The captain is our honored guest!

132
00:08:45.800 --> 00:08:48.340
Oh, right! Sorry!

133
00:08:48.340 --> 00:08:50.340
Don't worry, it's fine.

134
00:08:54.260 --> 00:08:55.970
Okay! Here we go!

135
00:08:56.720 --> 00:08:58.230
Damn fishmen...

136
00:08:58.230 --> 00:09:00.310
They make my skin crawl.

137
00:09:00.310 --> 00:09:02.440
But their money's good!

138
00:09:02.480 --> 00:09:06.900
East Gate, Arlong Park

139
00:09:17.450 --> 00:09:19.540
Hey, you! Out of the way!

140
00:09:20.580 --> 00:09:23.040
I'm here to kill Arlong!

141
00:09:23.040 --> 00:09:26.000
Arlong killed my daddy!

142
00:09:28.510 --> 00:09:31.050
Move, or I'll kill you, too!

143
00:09:31.680 --> 00:09:32.550
Hey!

144
00:09:36.510 --> 00:09:40.810
Arlong doesn't have time
to deal with brats like you!

145
00:09:42.650 --> 00:09:44.610
Get it? Now go home!

146
00:09:46.610 --> 00:09:49.990
Take this and look after yourself.

147
00:09:50.900 --> 00:09:52.700
Darn it!

148
00:10:00.580 --> 00:10:02.620
Oh! You're back, Nami!

149
00:10:02.620 --> 00:10:04.290
You were gone for a while!

150
00:10:04.290 --> 00:10:06.540
Well? How was your haul this time?

151
00:10:06.540 --> 00:10:08.670
I made a killing!

152
00:10:08.670 --> 00:10:11.340
There were plenty of suckers to scam!

153
00:10:11.340 --> 00:10:12.510
Check it out!

154
00:10:14.260 --> 00:10:16.470
Betrayal really is your forte!

155
00:10:17.010 --> 00:10:18.180
You flatter me.

156
00:10:18.810 --> 00:10:20.350
Hey! Brothers!

157
00:10:20.350 --> 00:10:23.140
Our comrade has
returned! Let's party!

158
00:10:24.230 --> 00:10:25.100
It's Nami!

159
00:10:25.100 --> 00:10:28.150
Nami's back!

160
00:10:28.190 --> 00:10:31.070
Officer Nami
Arlong Pirates

161
00:10:48.250 --> 00:10:52.760
W-W-We finally made it!
That's Arlong Park!

162
00:10:55.220 --> 00:10:59.850
So this is the hideout of Arlong,
the fishman from the Grand Line?!

163
00:11:01.520 --> 00:11:04.270
Could Nami really be here?

164
00:11:05.060 --> 00:11:08.860
Big Sis Nami was on the Going Merry,

165
00:11:08.860 --> 00:11:12.230
so let's check to make sure
it's docked on this island first!

166
00:11:12.230 --> 00:11:13.530
G-Good idea!

167
00:11:19.120 --> 00:11:20.450
We're busting in.

168
00:11:21.790 --> 00:11:24.910
Wh-Why are we
suddenly doing that?!

169
00:11:25.330 --> 00:11:28.790
Are you stupid?! We haven't
even found any clues yet!

170
00:11:29.210 --> 00:11:31.250
We're dealing with fishmen, you know!

171
00:11:31.250 --> 00:11:33.260
We gotta have a game plan!

172
00:11:33.260 --> 00:11:35.340
There's no time for that.

173
00:11:35.800 --> 00:11:39.350
Luffy told us to bring her back.

174
00:11:39.350 --> 00:11:41.760
And so we will, no matter
who we're dealing with!

175
00:11:42.390 --> 00:11:43.600
– Not good.
– Not good.

176
00:11:43.930 --> 00:11:44.980
Let's go!

177
00:11:52.190 --> 00:11:53.570
There it is! I found it!

178
00:11:53.940 --> 00:11:56.530
It's the Going Merry!
Why's it over there?

179
00:11:56.950 --> 00:12:00.370
So Big Sis Nami is here!

180
00:12:00.370 --> 00:12:04.450
Hey, you bastards!
What's the big idea?! Untie me!

181
00:12:04.870 --> 00:12:09.040
We're far to the east of Arlong Park...
at Cocoyashi Village.

182
00:12:09.040 --> 00:12:10.290
But it's strange.

183
00:12:10.290 --> 00:12:13.630
Why's the ship docked
so far from the village?

184
00:12:13.630 --> 00:12:15.460
I said to untie me!

185
00:12:15.840 --> 00:12:19.470
You nearly died from your injury!

186
00:12:19.470 --> 00:12:21.140
Just take it easy!

187
00:12:23.470 --> 00:12:26.100
Leave this one to me!

188
00:12:28.310 --> 00:12:31.690
I am so going to
chop him up someday!

189
00:12:31.690 --> 00:12:35.110
I'll bring that girl back!

190
00:12:36.570 --> 00:12:39.700
You're just happy she's
not actually at Arlong Park...

191
00:12:40.110 --> 00:12:42.030
Right rudder, full!

192
00:12:42.030 --> 00:12:44.660
Pull the boat up to the Going Merry!

193
00:12:44.660 --> 00:12:46.620
Right!

194
00:12:47.000 --> 00:12:48.410
Alright!

195
00:12:48.410 --> 00:12:52.000
I dub this brave moment,
in which I tread unknown soil,

196
00:12:52.000 --> 00:12:55.130
"Captain Usopp's Grand Adventure"!

197
00:13:04.970 --> 00:13:06.310
Are you alright?!

198
00:13:06.310 --> 00:13:07.470
There! There!

199
00:13:07.470 --> 00:13:09.230
Fishmen!

200
00:13:09.980 --> 00:13:11.520
Full speed ahead!

201
00:13:11.520 --> 00:13:12.940
Yes, sir!

202
00:13:15.190 --> 00:13:17.190
Why did you just pass by it?!

203
00:13:18.900 --> 00:13:21.910
Did you see that?!
There were fishmen there!

204
00:13:21.910 --> 00:13:25.080
That's Arlong's crew! They're scary!
Got a problem with that?!

205
00:13:25.080 --> 00:13:26.740
Don't you snap at me!

206
00:13:27.160 --> 00:13:31.210
Looks like this whole area
really is under Arlong's control!

207
00:13:31.710 --> 00:13:32.670
What now?

208
00:13:33.750 --> 00:13:36.460
Alright! We'll just say we
couldn't bring Nami back!

209
00:13:36.460 --> 00:13:39.920
Untie me, you idiots!

210
00:13:40.670 --> 00:13:42.220
Never seen that boat before...

211
00:13:42.220 --> 00:13:43.340
Suspicious...

212
00:13:46.260 --> 00:13:46.930
Time to go!

213
00:13:46.930 --> 00:13:47.640
Agreed!

214
00:13:47.640 --> 00:13:50.060
Wait just a damn minute, you two!

215
00:13:53.100 --> 00:13:54.310
– Bye!
– Bye!

216
00:13:54.810 --> 00:13:57.270
Hey! At least untie me!

217
00:14:03.410 --> 00:14:05.160
Wait, what? Just one guy?

218
00:14:05.160 --> 00:14:08.290
Are you some kinda
castaway or somethin'?

219
00:14:08.290 --> 00:14:10.000
I-I guess...

220
00:14:10.000 --> 00:14:11.960
I'm gonna kill those guys!

221
00:14:11.960 --> 00:14:14.790
Ah! So you got these wounds
from being tortured!

222
00:14:14.790 --> 00:14:18.250
Alright, let's take him
to Captain Arlong!

223
00:14:18.750 --> 00:14:19.880
Forgive us, Zoro!

224
00:14:19.880 --> 00:14:22.840
I'll tell Luffy you died honorably!

225
00:14:22.840 --> 00:14:24.840
What rotten luck!

226
00:14:24.840 --> 00:14:27.010
I'll never forget you, Big Bro!

227
00:14:27.010 --> 00:14:29.260
Alright, then! Let's get
on dry land for now!

228
00:14:29.260 --> 00:14:30.020
Right!

229
00:14:35.190 --> 00:14:38.270
There should be a town
called Gosa up here!

230
00:14:51.750 --> 00:14:56.080
Wh-What happened here?!

231
00:14:56.080 --> 00:15:00.590
I heard Arlong trashed it
a few weeks back, but...

232
00:15:00.590 --> 00:15:04.550
Th-The houses have all
been flipped upside down!

233
00:15:05.050 --> 00:15:10.510
It's said that fishmen are naturally
ten times stronger than humans...!

234
00:15:10.930 --> 00:15:15.520
Is this what people from
the Grand Line are capable of?

235
00:15:21.150 --> 00:15:24.190
How'd the street even get like this?

236
00:15:24.950 --> 00:15:28.070
A monster called Momoo did it.

237
00:15:28.070 --> 00:15:29.780
A monster?

238
00:15:30.780 --> 00:15:33.080
They have monsters, too?

239
00:15:33.500 --> 00:15:36.540
We brought him all the way
from the Grand Line.

240
00:15:37.330 --> 00:15:39.170
From the Grand Line, huh?

241
00:15:39.500 --> 00:15:42.050
Wait, we...?!

242
00:15:42.050 --> 00:15:44.920
You're with that castaway, right?!

243
00:15:47.470 --> 00:15:49.850
Bye-bye!

244
00:15:48.760 --> 00:15:49.850
Get back here!

245
00:15:50.300 --> 00:15:52.470
No way!

246
00:15:50.850 --> 00:15:52.470
Escaped by a hair...

247
00:15:53.600 --> 00:15:54.850
Please stay safe...

248
00:15:55.480 --> 00:15:56.770
Big Bro Usopp!

249
00:15:56.770 --> 00:15:59.770
I'm going to wait here for
Yosaku and Big Bro Luffy!

250
00:16:01.440 --> 00:16:04.780
Even if you're a fishman,
no one can catch me on dry land!

251
00:16:05.190 --> 00:16:07.280
I'm used to this!

252
00:16:07.280 --> 00:16:10.030
Catch me if you can!

253
00:16:11.990 --> 00:16:13.910
Wh-What the...?!

254
00:16:13.910 --> 00:16:15.870
I found you, fishman!

255
00:16:15.870 --> 00:16:19.080
This is for my daddy!
I'm gonna kill you!

256
00:16:23.420 --> 00:16:28.590
Nojiko
Cocoyashi Village
Chabo
Gosa Town

257
00:16:24.090 --> 00:16:25.760
Steer clear of fishmen!

258
00:16:25.760 --> 00:16:28.880
Don't forget, everyone here in Gosa

259
00:16:28.880 --> 00:16:33.060
was slaughtered because
a single villager defied them!

260
00:16:35.220 --> 00:16:36.270
Hold on...

261
00:16:36.270 --> 00:16:38.600
You look like a fishman,
but you're human.

262
00:16:38.600 --> 00:16:39.390
I think.

263
00:16:39.390 --> 00:16:41.060
You think?!

264
00:16:41.440 --> 00:16:43.440
Where are you?! Over there?!

265
00:16:43.940 --> 00:16:44.940
He's coming!

266
00:16:44.940 --> 00:16:46.440
A fishman!

267
00:16:46.440 --> 00:16:47.950
There was a real one, too?

268
00:16:50.530 --> 00:16:51.780
Get back!

269
00:16:52.410 --> 00:16:54.280
I, Captain Usopp, will protect you!

270
00:16:54.280 --> 00:16:56.250
I should be able to handle one!

271
00:16:58.000 --> 00:16:59.040
Take this!

272
00:16:59.040 --> 00:17:02.330
Lethal Lead Star–

273
00:17:08.840 --> 00:17:10.880
No one ever listens!

274
00:17:10.880 --> 00:17:13.510
I told you, mess with
the fishmen and we're dead!

275
00:17:14.260 --> 00:17:20.770
Outskirts of Cocoyashi Village

276
00:17:24.440 --> 00:17:26.320
Wh-Where am I?

277
00:17:26.320 --> 00:17:27.690
My house.

278
00:17:29.360 --> 00:17:30.700
You awake?

279
00:17:30.700 --> 00:17:31.860
Wh-Who are you?!

280
00:17:32.280 --> 00:17:34.030
I'm Nojiko.

281
00:17:34.030 --> 00:17:35.700
I grow tangerines here.

282
00:17:35.700 --> 00:17:38.700
That's right! You clobbered me!

283
00:17:39.250 --> 00:17:42.500
Just when I was trying
to save you, too!

284
00:17:42.830 --> 00:17:44.500
I'm the one who saved you.

285
00:17:45.840 --> 00:17:47.960
Had you done anything
to that fishman,

286
00:17:47.960 --> 00:17:50.550
there's no question you'd be dead.

287
00:17:50.550 --> 00:17:52.010
Damn out-of-towners!

288
00:17:54.300 --> 00:17:57.140
You, on the other hand,
are from Gosa, right?

289
00:17:58.100 --> 00:18:00.520
You should know
from firsthand experience

290
00:18:00.520 --> 00:18:04.860
that you'll be killed if you
provoke the fishmen.

291
00:18:04.860 --> 00:18:06.610
I know that...!

292
00:18:06.610 --> 00:18:10.820
I know that! But they killed my daddy!

293
00:18:11.360 --> 00:18:14.110
They stole everything,
destroyed our town,

294
00:18:14.110 --> 00:18:16.160
and killed tons of people!

295
00:18:16.160 --> 00:18:17.580
They have to pay!

296
00:18:17.580 --> 00:18:19.290
No matter what, they have to pay!

297
00:18:19.660 --> 00:18:23.040
That's why I went to Arlong Park!

298
00:18:23.040 --> 00:18:26.290
But a woman from his
crew got in the way!

299
00:18:29.420 --> 00:18:30.630
She...

300
00:18:30.630 --> 00:18:32.050
was like a witch!

301
00:18:32.840 --> 00:18:34.380
I hate this!

302
00:18:34.380 --> 00:18:37.010
I don't care if I die;
I'm going to avenge my daddy!

303
00:18:37.010 --> 00:18:38.260
Then die.

304
00:18:39.810 --> 00:18:42.770
If you're prepared to die,
then go get your revenge!

305
00:18:42.770 --> 00:18:44.730
But remember this:

306
00:18:44.730 --> 00:18:48.520
Now that the witch at Arlong Park
and I have stopped you,

307
00:18:48.940 --> 00:18:51.440
you've escaped death twice now!

308
00:18:52.820 --> 00:18:54.700
Leave when you're done with your tea.

309
00:18:54.700 --> 00:18:55.410
Hey!

310
00:18:55.410 --> 00:18:58.370
Can't you cut the kid some slack?!

311
00:18:58.370 --> 00:19:01.910
Kid or not, if someone wants
to die, then just let 'em die!

312
00:19:02.750 --> 00:19:06.210
He doesn't have the guts to live
through hard times anyway!

313
00:19:06.210 --> 00:19:07.330
What do you mean?

314
00:19:07.330 --> 00:19:10.880
I know a kid who's
focusing on the future,

315
00:19:10.880 --> 00:19:13.840
while she endures a life
more painful than death.

316
00:19:14.590 --> 00:19:19.970
That's why I hate people like him
who throw their lives away!

317
00:19:22.470 --> 00:19:26.100
What... What should I do, then?

318
00:19:26.690 --> 00:19:29.310
I'm so angry! But I'll endure it!

319
00:19:30.190 --> 00:19:31.270
What about your mom?

320
00:19:33.650 --> 00:19:35.280
She's alive...

321
00:19:37.200 --> 00:19:39.200
She must be worried sick.

322
00:19:39.200 --> 00:19:40.530
Go back to her.

323
00:19:52.300 --> 00:19:55.090
Despite the tattoos,
you're actually pretty nice!

324
00:19:55.090 --> 00:19:56.260
How closed-minded!

325
00:19:56.630 --> 00:19:59.220
I don't know anything
about you, you know.

326
00:19:59.220 --> 00:20:00.760
Oh, right!

327
00:20:01.100 --> 00:20:03.390
My name is Captain Usopp!

328
00:20:03.390 --> 00:20:05.520
I'm looking for a girl named Nami...

329
00:20:08.310 --> 00:20:11.520
What?! Nami's an officer
of the Arlong Pirates?!

330
00:20:11.940 --> 00:20:12.980
Yep.

331
00:20:12.980 --> 00:20:15.150
Everyone here knows about her.

332
00:20:15.150 --> 00:20:19.360
She's the "witch"
that little boy mentioned.

333
00:20:19.360 --> 00:20:23.200
Funnily enough, that witch
grew up in this very house.

334
00:20:27.710 --> 00:20:30.040
Nami and I are adopted sisters.

335
00:20:32.540 --> 00:20:34.210
So this is...

336
00:20:35.550 --> 00:20:37.130
Nami's house?

337
00:20:37.130 --> 00:20:39.760
Nami and I are both orphans.

338
00:20:40.300 --> 00:20:42.680
We were brought up in this house.

339
00:20:42.680 --> 00:20:45.060
Our foster parent is dead,

340
00:20:45.060 --> 00:20:49.270
but the three of us used to live
happily here in Cocoyashi Village.

341
00:20:52.020 --> 00:20:56.400
So, Nami betrayed
her own parent and village

342
00:20:56.400 --> 00:20:59.150
and joined Arlong's crew?!

343
00:20:59.490 --> 00:21:00.910
Yeah, pretty much.

344
00:21:00.910 --> 00:21:02.950
A real witch, huh?

345
00:21:03.780 --> 00:21:06.080
Dammit! So that's the deal?!

346
00:21:06.080 --> 00:21:08.710
She had us fooled the whole time!

347
00:21:08.710 --> 00:21:11.630
She was after treasure
from the very start!

348
00:21:11.630 --> 00:21:14.840
Even after she helped fight
to protect my village

349
00:21:14.840 --> 00:21:18.340
and looked so happy sailing with us!

350
00:21:18.970 --> 00:21:21.300
Oh? She looked happy?

351
00:21:23.090 --> 00:21:24.300
Her?

352
00:21:24.810 --> 00:21:28.140
We came here to
bring her back with us,

353
00:21:28.140 --> 00:21:30.310
but I guess there's no need for–

354
00:21:34.770 --> 00:21:40.490
That reminds me, a friend of ours
was unfortunately caught by the fishmen.

355
00:21:41.530 --> 00:21:43.410
This is bad...

356
00:21:43.410 --> 00:21:45.740
I wonder how he's holding up.

357
00:21:45.740 --> 00:21:48.080
Open the gate!

358
00:21:48.080 --> 00:21:50.540
We've brought someone suspicious!

359
00:22:01.090 --> 00:22:02.840
I'll ask again.

360
00:22:02.840 --> 00:22:05.850
Just why have you come here?

361
00:22:06.760 --> 00:22:11.100
I told you already—I'm looking
for a girl, you half-fish freak!

362
00:22:12.600 --> 00:22:15.610
You've got a big mouth
for a lowly human.

363
00:22:15.610 --> 00:22:19.070
I'll excuse you this time,
but never say "half-fish" again.

364
00:22:20.070 --> 00:22:23.030
We fishmen are evolved humans
who've gained the ability

365
00:22:23.030 --> 00:22:25.030
to breathe underwater.

366
00:22:25.030 --> 00:22:29.740
Our fish-like qualities
make us superior to you.

367
00:22:29.740 --> 00:22:34.210
Such traits are the proof
we've evolved far beyond you!

368
00:22:35.080 --> 00:22:39.590
Get it through your head that
fishmen are the lords of all things!

369
00:22:39.590 --> 00:22:44.180
Humans defying fishmen is basically
defying the laws of nature!

370
00:22:44.840 --> 00:22:48.310
I'm sick of your
ridiculous dogma, Arlong.

371
00:22:50.520 --> 00:22:52.930
Don't be like that, Nami.

372
00:22:52.930 --> 00:22:55.560
You may be human,
but you're an exception.

373
00:22:55.560 --> 00:22:59.360
You're a skilled cartographer and a
prized member of the Arlong Pirates!

374
00:22:59.360 --> 00:23:02.150
Your sea charts are second to none!

375
00:23:02.570 --> 00:23:05.780
I'm much smarter than you morons.

376
00:23:05.780 --> 00:23:06.990
It's only natural.

377
00:23:07.370 --> 00:23:08.240
Hey, Nami!

378
00:23:08.240 --> 00:23:09.950
What does he mean, “cartographer”?!

379
00:23:09.950 --> 00:23:13.160
Why are you acting all
buddy-buddy with this guy?!

380
00:23:13.160 --> 00:23:15.960
Oh? He's an acquaintance of yours?

381
00:23:15.960 --> 00:23:17.460
Don't be ridiculous!

382
00:23:17.460 --> 00:23:18.960
He was another mark.

383
00:23:18.960 --> 00:23:22.920
I just swiped a whole load
of treasure from this guy.

384
00:23:23.420 --> 00:23:27.430
I can't believe he'd follow me here
without any idea he'd been tricked.

385
00:23:27.430 --> 00:23:28.890
How naive.

386
00:23:29.510 --> 00:23:31.890
So these are your true colors, huh?

387
00:23:31.890 --> 00:23:34.390
After all that talk about hating pirates.

388
00:23:34.390 --> 00:23:35.890
Surprised?

389
00:23:35.890 --> 00:23:37.900
It was all an act.

390
00:23:37.900 --> 00:23:39.520
Does this clear things up?

391
00:23:42.150 --> 00:23:43.650
Th-That's...

392
00:23:51.200 --> 00:23:54.040
I'm a pirate, plain and simple!

393
00:23:54.040 --> 00:23:56.080
An officer of the Arlong Pirates!

394
00:23:58.670 --> 00:24:00.920
Boy, she sure had you fooled!

395
00:24:01.670 --> 00:24:03.920
This girl is a cold-blooded witch;

396
00:24:03.920 --> 00:24:08.130
she'll even overlook the death
of her own parent for money!

397
00:24:09.340 --> 00:24:10.100
Well...

398
00:24:10.600 --> 00:24:14.020
just chalk it up to bad luck that
you crossed her and give up.

399
00:24:14.020 --> 00:24:15.770
I see.

400
00:24:16.640 --> 00:24:21.230
Though, it's not like I ever
trusted her to begin with.

401
00:24:21.560 --> 00:24:25.190
Even if she were a mass murderer,
I wouldn't be too surprised.

402
00:24:25.190 --> 00:24:28.700
In that case, can't you just get lost?!
I'm sick of looking at you!

403
00:24:40.580 --> 00:24:43.840
What happened?! Why'd he
suddenly jump into the water?!

404
00:24:43.840 --> 00:24:46.300
Is this some kind of trick?!

405
00:24:46.720 --> 00:24:49.720
No, it's not like he slipped or anything...

406
00:24:49.720 --> 00:24:51.010
Then he ran away!

407
00:24:51.430 --> 00:24:55.970
No, his arms and legs are tied!
He can't swim like that!

408
00:24:55.970 --> 00:24:57.060
It's suicide.

409
00:24:57.730 --> 00:24:58.940
Leave him be.

410
00:25:02.520 --> 00:25:04.070
That idiot!

411
00:25:16.750 --> 00:25:17.620
He's back.

412
00:25:17.620 --> 00:25:20.290
Hey! What's going on, Nami?!

413
00:25:22.710 --> 00:25:23.960
What were you thinking?!

414
00:25:26.840 --> 00:25:29.170
No, what were you thinking?

415
00:25:32.180 --> 00:25:35.680
You're just a little girl who
can't even watch one guy die...

416
00:25:35.680 --> 00:25:37.140
Stop trying to act cool!

417
00:25:38.640 --> 00:25:42.100
Save me sooner next time, idiot!
I thought I was gonna drown!

418
00:25:42.980 --> 00:25:44.560
Screw you!

419
00:25:46.110 --> 00:25:48.400
Mess with me again and I'll kill you!

420
00:25:49.190 --> 00:25:50.400
I wonder.

421
00:25:51.740 --> 00:25:53.530
You're covered in bandages.

422
00:25:53.530 --> 00:25:56.830
I didn't have a change of clothes,
so I used these instead.

423
00:26:05.630 --> 00:26:07.090
Hey, Nami.

424
00:26:07.090 --> 00:26:08.590
What should we do with him?

425
00:26:08.590 --> 00:26:09.920
Lock him up!

426
00:26:09.920 --> 00:26:11.630
I'll deal with him myself!

427
00:26:11.630 --> 00:26:14.390
Captain Arlong! Captain Arlong!

428
00:26:15.680 --> 00:26:17.310
What is it, brother?

429
00:26:17.680 --> 00:26:18.470
I'm sorry!

430
00:26:18.470 --> 00:26:24.980
That guy had a long-nosed
friend with him, but he got away!

431
00:26:24.980 --> 00:26:27.150
What the hell, Usopp?!

432
00:26:27.150 --> 00:26:29.320
You wound up getting
spotted anyway?!

433
00:26:29.320 --> 00:26:30.360
I think...

434
00:26:30.360 --> 00:26:33.490
he might've escaped into
Cocoyashi Village...

435
00:26:34.160 --> 00:26:35.740
Cocoyashi Village, huh?

436
00:26:36.370 --> 00:26:37.740
Perfect.

437
00:26:37.740 --> 00:26:39.700
I have some business there, too.

438
00:26:45.380 --> 00:26:48.040
Cocoyashi Village

439
00:26:45.960 --> 00:26:48.040
Hey! Arlong's coming!

440
00:26:48.040 --> 00:26:49.590
What?!

441
00:26:49.590 --> 00:26:51.300
What for?!

442
00:26:51.300 --> 00:26:53.590
We just paid our tribute!

443
00:26:54.510 --> 00:26:58.470
It's probably about my
weapons they discovered.

444
00:26:58.470 --> 00:27:00.520
Return to your houses, everyone.

445
00:27:00.520 --> 00:27:01.890
Mr. Gen...!

446
00:27:02.810 --> 00:27:03.980
They're here!

447
00:27:12.400 --> 00:27:14.530
So you're the bastard...

448
00:27:14.530 --> 00:27:17.700
who was in possession of weapons.

449
00:27:17.700 --> 00:27:19.740
Yes, that's correct.

450
00:27:19.740 --> 00:27:24.750
I've always loved collecting weapons.

451
00:27:19.780 --> 00:27:24.120
Genzo
Cocoyashi Village

452
00:27:24.750 --> 00:27:28.710
Are collections forbidden
under your rule, as well?

453
00:27:29.170 --> 00:27:31.250
Yes, I can't allow that.

454
00:27:31.710 --> 00:27:34.590
Weapons breed nothing but
evil thoughts and violence.

455
00:27:34.590 --> 00:27:37.720
They're the primary cause
of disturbing the peace.

456
00:27:39.050 --> 00:27:41.680
He's huge! That's Arlong?!

457
00:27:41.680 --> 00:27:43.270
H-He's not human!

458
00:27:43.270 --> 00:27:45.350
Right. Because he's a fishman.

459
00:27:45.350 --> 00:27:46.230
Oh, right.

460
00:27:46.560 --> 00:27:49.810
I control twenty towns and villages.

461
00:27:49.810 --> 00:27:54.070
As their overseer,
I can't afford to have rebellions.

462
00:27:54.070 --> 00:27:59.780
I destroyed the great port town of Gosa
as an example to the other communities!

463
00:27:59.780 --> 00:28:01.990
Being unable to pay tribute

464
00:28:02.450 --> 00:28:05.330
is an act of rebellion against us!

465
00:28:05.330 --> 00:28:06.460
Hey!

466
00:28:06.460 --> 00:28:07.830
Pay tribute?

467
00:28:07.830 --> 00:28:09.210
Exactly as it sounds.

468
00:28:09.210 --> 00:28:11.290
It's money that we offer to them.

469
00:28:11.790 --> 00:28:15.800
Every month, we buy
our lives with money.

470
00:28:15.800 --> 00:28:17.800
Adults and children...

471
00:28:17.800 --> 00:28:20.800
If anyone in a village can't
pay the tribute money...

472
00:28:20.800 --> 00:28:22.890
even if it's just one person...

473
00:28:22.890 --> 00:28:25.640
the village will get
annihilated just like Gosa.

474
00:28:25.640 --> 00:28:29.230
Then that huge town was destroyed
just because of one person?!

475
00:28:29.230 --> 00:28:31.020
That's how Arlong governs.

476
00:28:31.480 --> 00:28:35.440
They're species-obsessed and don't
give a damn about killing humans.

477
00:28:35.440 --> 00:28:36.820
Listen up.

478
00:28:36.820 --> 00:28:41.950
Puny humans shouldn't worry about
anything except continuing to pay up!

479
00:28:42.700 --> 00:28:46.080
I need vast sums of capital!

480
00:28:46.080 --> 00:28:50.210
Your tribute money will eventually
become the cornerstone

481
00:28:50.210 --> 00:28:53.420
of the Arlong Empire,
which will rule the East Blue!

482
00:28:55.000 --> 00:28:57.300
A-Arlong Empire?!

483
00:28:58.800 --> 00:29:03.470
They're planning to turn the entire
East Blue into a fishman empire?!

484
00:29:23.240 --> 00:29:24.870
Get out of here.

485
00:29:24.870 --> 00:29:26.870
Before Arlong comes back.
